# BRIKA Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Project Overview

BRIKA (Event-driven Logical Intelligence Architecture) is a Bun-first home automation runtime with:
- Isolated plugin processes communicating via binary IPC
- Block-based visual workflow engine
- React UI with TanStack Router/Query and React Flow

## Architecture Boundaries

NEVER cross these boundaries:
- Hub NEVER imports plugin code directly (uses IPC)
- Plugins ONLY depend on @brika/sdk and @brika/shared
- UI ONLY imports from @brika/shared (no SDK)

## ID Naming Convention

Always use this format:
- Plugin ID: Full package.json name (e.g., `@brika/plugin-timer`)
- Tool ID: `pluginId:toolId` (e.g., `@brika/plugin-timer:set`)
- Block ID: `pluginId:blockId` (e.g., `@brika/blocks-builtin:condition`)

## Key Files

When working on:
- **Plugin loading**: `apps/hub/src/runtime/plugins/plugin-manager.ts`
- **Tool definitions**: `packages/sdk/src/tool.ts`
- **Block definitions**: `packages/sdk/src/blocks/define.ts`
- **Workflow execution**: `apps/hub/src/runtime/automations/workflow-executor.ts`
- **API endpoints**: `apps/hub/src/runtime/http/api-server.ts`
- **UI features**: `apps/ui/src/features/<feature>/`

## Coding Style

### TypeScript
- Use `@singleton()` decorator for DI services
- Use `inject(ServiceClass)` for property injection
- Use `#` for private class members
- Return structured results, never throw across IPC:
  ```typescript
  return { ok: true, content: "..." };
  return { ok: false, content: "Error..." };
  ```

### Plugin Development
```typescript
// Always match package.json name
const { api, start, use } = createPluginRuntime({
  id: "@brika/plugin-name",  // From package.json
  version: "0.1.0",
});

// Define tools with Zod schemas
export const myTool = defineTool({
  id: "action",  // Local ID only
  description: "...",
  schema: z.object({ ... }),
}, async (args) => {
  return { ok: true, content: "..." };
});

use(myTool);  // Register tool
await start();  // Start plugin loop
```

### Block Development
```typescript
export const myBlock = defineBlock({
  id: "my-block",  // Local ID only
  name: "Display Name",
  description: "...",
  category: "flow",
  icon: "lucide-icon-name",
  color: "#hexcolor",
  inputs: [{ id: "in", name: "Input" }],
  outputs: [{ id: "out", name: "Output" }],
  schema: z.object({ ... }),
}, async (config, ctx, runtime) => {
  return { output: "out", data: result };
});
```

### UI Components
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`
- Follow feature module pattern: `api.ts`, `hooks.ts`, `Page.tsx`
- Use TanStack Query for server state
- Use Zustand for client state (SSE streams)

## Common Patterns

### Adding Hub Service
```typescript
import { singleton, inject } from "@brika/di";

@singleton()
export class MyService {
  private readonly logs = inject(Logger);
  private readonly events = inject(EventBus);
}
```

### Adding API Endpoint
In `api-server.ts`:
```typescript
if (p === "/api/myendpoint" && m === "GET") {
  return json(this.myService.list());
}
```

### Adding UI Feature
```
features/myfeature/
├── index.ts           # export { MyPage } from "./MyPage"
├── MyPage.tsx         # React component
├── api.ts             # API functions
└── hooks.ts           # React Query hooks
```

## Don't

- Don't use `console.log` in plugins (breaks IPC)
- Don't use `any` type without `biome-ignore` comment
- Don't create abstractions for one-time operations
- Don't add features beyond what's requested
- Don't import Hub code in plugins or vice versa

## Testing

- Hub tests: `apps/hub/src/__tests__/`
- SDK tests: `packages/sdk/src/__tests__/`
- Run with: `bun test`

## Configuration

- Main config: `brika.yml`
- Workflows: `automations/*.yml`
- Plugin schema: `packages/sdk/brika-plugin.schema.json`



